Class SinglyLinkedList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • lab02.SinglyLinkedList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The data type for the list
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LinkedBag

    public class SinglyLinkedList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    A data structure that holds items in a list loosely connected. Each element holds its own information as well as the location of the next element.

      • addLast

        public void addLast(T t)
        Creates a new Node. Adds the Node at the very end of the list. The previous tail is connected to the new Node
        Parameters:
        t - The element to be used to create a new Node

      • removeFirst

        public T removeFirst()
        Accessor and Mutator Method. Removes the first item in the list if possible. Returns the element of the next Node if the removal is successful.
        Returns:
        Null for an empty list, the element of the new first Node otherwise
